        "\n",
        "## Introduction\n",
        "\n",
        "Python is one of the most popular programming languages in the world, known for its simplicity and versatility. Whether you're interested in web development, data science, or automation, Python is an excellent choice to start your programming journey.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why Python?\n",
        "\n",
        "Python offers several advantages for beginners:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Easy to Learn**: Clean and readable syntax\n",
        "- **Versatile**: Used in web development, data science, AI, and more\n",
        "- **Large Community**: Extensive libraries and support\n",
        "- **High Demand**: Popular in the job market\n",
        "\n",
        "## Basic Python Syntax\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's explore some fundamental Python concepts.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Variables and Data Types"
      ],
      "id": "0a051c7b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Variables in Python\n",
        "name = \"Alice\"\n",
        "age = 25\n",
        "height = 5.6\n",
        "is_student = True\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Name: {name}, Age: {age}\")"
      ],
      "id": "d95c600b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Lists and Loops"
      ],
      "id": "ef614b71"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Working with lists\n",
        "fruits = [\"apple\", \"banana\", \"orange\", \"grape\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "for fruit in fruits:\n",
        "    print(f\"I like {fruit}s\")"
      ],
      "id": "c4183adb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Functions"
      ],
      "id": "c126cecd"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Defining a simple function\n",
        "def greet(name):\n",
        "    return f\"Hello, {name}! Welcome to Python programming.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calling the function\n",
        "message = greet(\"Sarah\")\n",
        "print(message)"
      ],
